re introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William Lowell was born in 1315, in Yardley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. He had at least 1 son with Margaret Littleton. He died about 1375, in his hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1315–Abt 1375":"1315–umbes 1375","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1315–1375":"1315–1375","1315":"1315","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","Abt 1375":"umbes 1375","1375":"1375","Yardly, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Yardley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1315–Abt 1375":"1315–noin 1375","1315–Female":"1315–Kuollut","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1315–1375":"1315–1375","1315":"1315","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","Abt 1375":"noin 1375","1375":"1375","Yardly, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Yardley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1315–Abt 1375":"1315–environ 1375","1315–Female":"1315–Décédée","1345–1400":"1345–1400","1315–1375":"1315–1375","1315":"1315","1345":"1345","1400":"1400","Abt 1375":"environ 1375","1375":"1375","Yardly, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Yardley, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom":"Yardley, Worcestershire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Wi